rules.content:
(1) The Secretary of the Parliamentary Affairs Division shall assess the status of business pending before the Assembly, the Senate, or a joint sitting.
(2) In accordance with Rule 15-A, the Secretary Parliamentary Affairs Division shall obtain the President's orders for summoning the relevant House(s) and communicate the session's date, time, and venue to:
(a) the Secretary of the Assembly, if it concerns the Assembly;
(b) the Secretary of the Senate, if it concerns the Senate;
(c) both Secretaries, if it concerns both Houses or a joint sitting.
(3) Upon receiving this communication, the session's schedule shall be notified in the Gazette by:
(a) the Secretary of the Assembly, for the Assembly;
(b) the Secretary of the Senate, for the Senate;
(c) both Secretaries, for joint sittings or both Houses.

(1) The Secretary Parliamentary Affairs Division shall, under Rule 15-A, obtain the President's orders for prorogation and communicate the information to:
(a) the Secretary of the Assembly, if it concerns the Assembly;
(b) the Secretary of the Senate, if it concerns the Senate;
(c) both Secretaries, if it concerns both Houses or a joint sitting.
(2) After receiving this communication, the prorogation shall be notified in the Gazette by:
(a) the Secretary of the Assembly, for the Assembly;
(b) the Secretary of the Senate, for the Senate;
(c) both Secretaries, for joint sittings or both Houses.
